        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 6 at 3:15PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Barrington, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mettawa, Wauconda, Lake Bluff, Fox River Grove, Port Barrington,
Hawthorn Woods, Deer Park, Highwood, Winthrop Harbor, Deerfield,
Hainesville, Grayslake, Highland Park, Inverness, South Barrington,
Gurnee, Tower Lakes, Vernon Hills, Buffalo Grove, Libertyville,
Waukegan, Wadsworth, Third Lake, North Chicago, and Barrington Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
